'''Sōma Shrine''' (相馬神社) is a Shinto shrine located in Nakamura, Sōma City, Fukushima Prefecture. It is built on the site of the former {{ill|Nakamura Castle (Mutsu Province)|ja|相馬中村城|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakamura Castle (Mutsu Province)|qq=}}. Under the {{ill|modern shrine Ranking system|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|1=Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/modern shrine Ranking system|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=}}, it held the status of a prefectural shrine (県社). The shrine is one of several established during the late Edo and early Meiji periods to honor domain founders.

The enshrined deities are {{ill|Ame-no-Minakanushi|lt=Ame-no-Minakanushi no Kami|ja|天之御中主大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Minakanushi|qq=}}, identified with {{ill|Myōken|lt=Myōken Bosatsu|ja|妙見菩薩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōken|qq=}}, and {{ill|Taira no Masakado|ja|Taira no Masakado|1=Taira no Masakado|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Masakado|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Masakado|qq=}}, the tutelary deity of the {{ill|Sōma clan|ja|相馬氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōma clan|qq=}}.

== Overview ==
Sōma Shrine was established in {{ill|1880|ja|明治13年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1880|qq=}} to enshrine {{ill|Sōma Moritsune|ja|相馬師常|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōma Moritsune|qq=}}, the founder of the Sōma clan. The shrine is located within {{ill|Baryō Park|ja|馬陵公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Baryō Park|qq=}}, which encompasses the ruins of Nakamura Castle. 

The park also contains the {{ill|Sōma Nakamura Shrine|ja|相馬中村神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sōma Nakamura Shrine|qq=}}, which is sometimes referred to as Myōken Nakamura Shrine. Despite their proximity, Sōma Shrine and Sōma Nakamura Shrine are separate entities. Additionally, other shrines related to the Sōma clan include {{ill|Myōken Ōta Shrine|ja|妙見太田神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōken Ōta Shrine|qq=}} in Haramachi and {{ill|Myōken Odaka Shrine|ja|妙見小高神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōken Odaka Shrine|qq=}} in Odaka, both located in what is now {{ill|Minamisōma City|ja|南相馬市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamisōma City|qq=}}. Collectively, these shrines are commonly referred to as Nakamura Shrine, Ōta Shrine, and Odaka Shrine.

